Rub roast with KC Masterpiece(R) Steak Seasoning with Garlic on all sides, coating well. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat; brown roast on all sides, about 10 minutes. Place roast in a 6-quart slow cooker. Pour KC Masterpiece(R) Original Barbecue Sauce and pasta sauce over meat. Place mushrooms, onion, carrots, celery and potatoes around meat. Cover and cook on high setting 5 hours or on low setting 8 hours, or until meat is tender and vegetables are cooked. Remove meat and vegetables from slow cooker. To serve, slice meat and serve with gravy and vegetables. Sprinkle with fresh parsley, to taste.